The method `hitBricks` takes two parameters: `grid` (a 2D array representing the initial state of the grid) and `hits` (a 2D array representing the positions of bricks to be erased).
The `grid` parameter should not be null.
The `hits` parameter should not be null.
The `grid` parameter should have at least one row and one column.
The `hits` parameter should have at least one row and two columns.
The values in the `hits` parameter should be valid positions within the `grid` parameter.
The `grid` parameter should only contain 0s and 1s, where 0 represents an empty cell and 1 represents a brick.
